parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the automatic seat belt can cause the belt to stick or malfunction, leading to a increased risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt light comes on
the seat belt sticks or gets stuck
the belt refuses to move on the rail
the buzzer comes on while driving
the belt tends to move slightly up and down while driving
the belt locks into place and will not move
the belt moves forward unexpectedly
the belt tightens severely
the belt chokes the passenger.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the passive seat belt buckle can cause the belt to stick or malfunction, leading to a increased risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The passive seat belt buckle stays at the rearmost position
the belt pins the driver in the vehicle
the belt causes minor abrasion to the driver's neck
the belt locks into place and will not move.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt retractor can cause the belt to stick or malfunction, leading to a increased risk of injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt retractor fails
the belt will not retract
the belt gets jammed
the belt moves forward unexpectedly
the belt tightens severely.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Filler Neck Corrosion and Rusting
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion and rusting of the fuel filler neck can lead to a fire hazard when gasoline is put into the car, as it can compromise the integrity of the metal and cause a leak or ignition.
symptoms: Corrosion and rusting of the fuel filler neck
fuel leaks
strong gasoline smell
flames coming out of the fuel tank when opening the gas cap.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel tank leaks can cause a fire hazard, as gasoline can spill onto the road or surrounding areas, and potentially ignite.
symptoms: Fuel leaks
strong gasoline smell
holes in the fuel tank
excessive fuel leakage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The ignition of fuel vapors or liquid fuel can cause a fire hazard, potentially leading to serious injury or damage.
symptoms: Flames coming out of the fuel tank when opening the gas cap
flames coming out of the fuel tank when filling up with fuel.
